    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-06-11</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-07-10T16:29:18Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>End Police Use of Chokeholds Act of 2020</b></p> <p>This bill creates a new condition of eligibility for funds under the Edward Byrne Memorial Justice Assistance Grant (JAG) program and the Community Oriented Policing Services (COPS) program.</p> <p>Specifically, to be eligible for grant funds under the COPS program and JAG program, a state or locality must have in effect a law that prohibits law enforcement officers from using a chokehold or carotid hold. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
